The paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning techniques to identify and categorize online learning resources mentioned in MOOC discussion forums. This falls under the sub-category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also addresses challenges related to diversity of expressions and long-range contextual dependencies, which are common in NLP tasks and can be addressed using techniques from information retrieval (cs.IR), machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI), and deep learning (cs.DL).
